    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Appointment
    class that creates objects to hold patient information and further information about appointment
    ClinicManagerController
    this class acts as the Controller in the MVC style of this software, controlling what the user sees, processing data, and processing appointments
    ClinicManagerMain
     
    Commands
    class to run and process commands
    Date
    Represents a date with methods for validation and comparison.
    Doctor
    Class to hold information about Doctors, a subclass of Provider
    Imaging
    Class that holds information about imaging appointments, a subclass of Appointment
    List<E>
    This class provides various methods to manipulate and access the elements in the list.
    Location
    enum class that holds the locations, city, counties and zipcodes of the locations associated with clinic
    Patient
    subclass of person that holds patient information for appointments and medical record
    Person
    Person class is the parent class of Patient and Provider and provides the profiles of both
    Profile
    class to hold first name, last name and date of birth of a given person
    Provider
    abstract class that holds information about a given provider including location and rate
    Radiology
    The Radiology enum defines the types of available imaging services.
    Sort
    class used to sort a generic list in different ways using different keys
    Specialty
    enum class that holds the different specialties a provider can specialize in
    Technician
    a subclass of provider that specialize in imaging services
    Timeslot
    This class supports comparison and provides static methods for creating predefined time slots.
    Visit
    Represents a visit in a linked list of appointments.
